OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FWagner boss: It's prisoners
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Ffighting, or your children 
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A Russian mercenary boss has defended  
OL,6, the idea of sending prisoners to fight 
OL,7, in the Ukraine war after a video showed
OL,8, him recruiting at a prison.            
OL,10,FYevgeny Prigozhin, head of the Wagner  
OL,11,Fgroup, said those who do not want to   
OL,12,Fsend convicts to fight should send     
OL,13,Ftheir own children instead.            
OL,15,FEarlier, leaked footage showed him     
OL,16,Ftelling inmates they would be freed if 
OL,17,Fthey served six months with his group. 
OL,19,FThe Wagner group is believed to have   
OL,20,Fbeen fighting in Ukraine since 2014.   
